In Part II, implement the Josephus game as a circular linked list. The driver plays the game twice, once with integers, which finds the winning position, and again with names.  After reading the names Michael, Hannah, Jacob, Ruth, and Matthew, your circular linked list should point to the last name, Matthew, like this:
 
 
 
 
 
This time, replace the name at the winning position with "Josephus", so that Josephus will always win.
 
